29#include <sys/cdefs.h>
30#ifndef lint
31__RCSID("$NetBSD: print-mpls.c,v 1.8 2017/09/08 14:01:13 christos Exp $");
32#endif
33
34/* \summary: Multi-Protocol Label Switching (MPLS) printer */
35
36#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
37#include "config.h"
38#endif
39
40#include <netdissect-stdinc.h>
41
42#include "netdissect.h"
43#include "extract.h"
44#include "mpls.h"
45
46static const char *mpls_labelname[] = {
47/*0*/ "IPv4 explicit NULL", "router alert", "IPv6 explicit NULL",
48 "implicit NULL", "rsvd",
49/*5*/ "rsvd", "rsvd", "rsvd", "rsvd", "rsvd",
50/*10*/ "rsvd", "rsvd", "rsvd", "rsvd", "rsvd",
51/*15*/ "rsvd",
52};
53
54enum mpls_packet_type {
55 PT_UNKNOWN,
56 PT_IPV4,
57 PT_IPV6,
58 PT_OSI
59};
60
61/*
62 * RFC3032: MPLS label stack encoding
63 */
64void
65mpls_print(netdissect_options *ndo, const u_char *bp, u_int length)
66{
67 const u_char *p;
68 uint32_t label_entry;
69 uint16_t label_stack_depth = 0;
70 enum mpls_packet_type pt = PT_UNKNOWN;
71
72 p = bp;
73 ND_PRINT((ndo, "MPLS"));
74 do {
75 ND_TCHECK2(*p, sizeof(label_entry));
76 if (length < sizeof(label_entry)) {
77 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|MPLS], length %u", length));
78 return;
79 }
80 label_entry = EXTRACT_32BITS(p);
81 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s(label %u",
82 (label_stack_depth && ndo->ndo_vflag) ? "\n\t" : " ",
83 MPLS_LABEL(label_entry)));
84 label_stack_depth++;
85 if (ndo->ndo_vflag &&
86 MPLS_LABEL(label_entry) < sizeof(mpls_labelname) / sizeof(mpls_labelname[0]))
87 ND_PRINT((ndo, " (%s)", mpls_labelname[MPLS_LABEL(label_entry)]));
88 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", exp %u", MPLS_EXP(label_entry)));
89 if (MPLS_STACK(label_entry))
90 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", [S]"));
91 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", ttl %u)", MPLS_TTL(label_entry)));
92
93 p += sizeof(label_entry);
94 length -= sizeof(label_entry);
95 } while (!MPLS_STACK(label_entry));
96
97 /*
98 * Try to figure out the packet type.
99 */
100 switch (MPLS_LABEL(label_entry)) {
101
102 case 0: /* IPv4 explicit NULL label */
103 case 3: /* IPv4 implicit NULL label */
104 pt = PT_IPV4;
105 break;
106
107 case 2: /* IPv6 explicit NULL label */
108 pt = PT_IPV6;
109 break;
110
111 default:
112 /*
113 * Generally there's no indication of protocol in MPLS label
114 * encoding.
115 *
116 * However, draft-hsmit-isis-aal5mux-00.txt describes a
117 * technique for encapsulating IS-IS and IP traffic on the
118 * same ATM virtual circuit; you look at the first payload
119 * byte to determine the network layer protocol, based on
120 * the fact that
121 *
122 * 1) the first byte of an IP header is 0x45-0x4f
123 * for IPv4 and 0x60-0x6f for IPv6;
124 *
125 * 2) the first byte of an OSI CLNP packet is 0x81,
126 * the first byte of an OSI ES-IS packet is 0x82,
127 * and the first byte of an OSI IS-IS packet is
128 * 0x83;
129 *
130 * so the network layer protocol can be inferred from the
131 * first byte of the packet, if the protocol is one of the
132 * ones listed above.
133 *
134 * Cisco sends control-plane traffic MPLS-encapsulated in
135 * this fashion.
136 */
137 ND_TCHECK(*p);
138 if (length < 1) {
139 /* nothing to print */
140 return;
141 }
142 switch(*p) {
143
144 case 0x45:
145 case 0x46:
146 case 0x47:
147 case 0x48:
148 case 0x49:
149 case 0x4a:
150 case 0x4b:
151 case 0x4c:
152 case 0x4d:
153 case 0x4e:
154 case 0x4f:
155 pt = PT_IPV4;
156 break;
157
158 case 0x60:
159 case 0x61:
160 case 0x62:
161 case 0x63:
162 case 0x64:
163 case 0x65:
164 case 0x66:
165 case 0x67:
166 case 0x68:
167 case 0x69:
168 case 0x6a:
169 case 0x6b:
170 case 0x6c:
171 case 0x6d:
172 case 0x6e:
173 case 0x6f:
174 pt = PT_IPV6;
175 break;
176
177 case 0x81:
178 case 0x82:
179 case 0x83:
180 pt = PT_OSI;
181 break;
182
183 default:
184 /* ok bail out - we did not figure out what it is*/
185 break;
186 }
187 }
188
189 /*
190 * Print the payload.
191 */
192 if (pt == PT_UNKNOWN) {
193 if (!ndo->ndo_suppress_default_print)
194 ND_DEFAULTPRINT(p, length);
195 return;
196 }
197 ND_PRINT((ndo, ndo->ndo_vflag ? "\n\t" : " "));
198 switch (pt) {
199
200 case PT_IPV4:
201 ip_print(ndo, p, length);
202 break;
203
204 case PT_IPV6:
205 ip6_print(ndo, p, length);
206 break;
207
208 case PT_OSI:
209 isoclns_print(ndo, p, length);
210 break;
211
212 default:
213 break;
214 }
215 return;
216
217trunc:
218 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|MPLS]"));
219}
